claim.claim-text:
4. A method for manufacturing multilayered components, comprising the steps of: 
mixing a composition represented by the formula A′xA″1-xB′yB″1-yO4 with either one of a sintering aid and an additive, to form a slurry, said A′ and said A″ being elements selected from the group consisting of La, Nd, Y and Al, said said B′ and B″ being elements selected from the group consisting of Nb and Ta, and said x and said y being mole fractions, in the range of 0≦x≦1.0, and 0≦y≦1.0, respectively; 
deaerating said slurry, followed by molding said slurry into a tape form; 
printing an inner electrode on said molded tape form by use of a low melting point electrode paste with a melting point of about 1,000° C. or lower; 
laminating said inner electrode-printed tape to at least two layers; and 
sintering said laminated tape in a sintering furnace at about 1000° C. or lower.
